Sentencas: Double perovskite, Sr2Fe2-xMoxO6-delta (SFMO), as an anode material of the solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) exhibits excellent performance.
Titulo: Sr2Fe2-xMoxO6-δ perovskite as an anode in a solid oxide fuel cell: Effect of the substitution ratio

Sentencas: The effects of the substitution ratio of Mo on its properties and electro-catalytic activity are examined.
Titulo: Sr2Fe2-xMoxO6-δ perovskite as an anode in a solid oxide fuel cell: Effect of the substitution ratio

Sentencas: The SFMO anode shows a porous structure with a pore size of several micrometers.
Titulo: Sr2Fe2-xMoxO6-δ perovskite as an anode in a solid oxide fuel cell: Effect of the substitution ratio

Sentencas: Using hydrogen and dry methanol as the fuels, the single cell with the SFMO anode with x between 0.4 and 0.6 gives the maximum power outputs of 541 and 387 mW cm(-2) at 1073 K, respectively.
Titulo: Sr2Fe2-xMoxO6-δ perovskite as an anode in a solid oxide fuel cell: Effect of the substitution ratio

Sentencas: The electro-catalytic activity of SFMO anodes exhibits an order of Sr2Fe1.4Mo0.6O6-delta > Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta >
Titulo: Sr2Fe2-xMoxO6-δ perovskite as an anode in a solid oxide fuel cell: Effect of the substitution ratio
Sr2Fe2-xMoxO6-δ perovskite as an anode in a solid oxide fuel cell: Effect of the substitution ratio

Sentencas: However, the overall conductivity of SFMO displays a reverse order.
Titulo: Sr2Fe2-xMoxO6-δ perovskite as an anode in a solid oxide fuel cell: Effect of the substitution ratio

Sentencas: With the increase of the Mo content, the surface Fe2+/Fe3+ ratio increases regularly, but the Mo5+/Mo6+ radio shows a peak in Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta.
Titulo: Sr2Fe2-xMoxO6-δ perovskite as an anode in a solid oxide fuel cell: Effect of the substitution ratio

Sentencas: It is concluded that the electro-activity of the SFMO anodes for the electro-oxidation of hydrogen and methanol is not limited by their conductivity, but their surface Fe2+/Fe3+ redox couple.
Titulo: Sr2Fe2-xMoxO6-δ perovskite as an anode in a solid oxide fuel cell: Effect of the substitution ratio
